Cell.Data: Summary of procedure and content of Worksheets:

Cell.ss:Data: The attached worksheet, "Metabolic_Network" contains the metabolic network reconstruction for C.acetobutylicum. The network presented in this appendix is specific for growth in minimal media (Monot et al., 1982). The first column gives the KEGG pathway annotation in which the reaction is located. A reaction may be located within multiple KEGG pathways. In this instance, the reaction is presented for each pathway (a reaction may appear multiple times in the worksheet). For each reaction, the locus number(s) and gene name(s) (if known) of all genes encoding the enzyme(s) that catalyze the particular reaction are given. All Enzyme Commission (EC) numbers are given for enzymes present in C. acetobutylicum that catalyze the particular reaction. For some reactions, this information is unknown. In these cases, the information is listed as "not available" (N/A). More detailed information of C. acetobutylicum membrane transporters is not presented here. Enzymes found non-essential to biomass generation through involvement in broken or incomplete pathways are listed in the "Non-Essential_Enzymes" worksheet.

ss:Data.Font: secretes the protonated species of weak acids. These species then dissociate in the extracellular medium according to given pKa and pH values. Protonated weak acids in membrane transport equations are denoted with "-H" (e.g., butyrate-H).

Cell.ss:Data: Each reaction of the metabolic network was systematically knocked-out (constrained to zero flux) and FBA was applied. If the resulting specific growth rate was greater than zero (reaction not essential for growth), the reaction was labeled "1." Those reactions resulting in arrested growth in silico when knocked-out are labeled "0."

Cell.Data: This analysis was performed for minimal media, a partially-supplemented media and a supplemented media. Culture growth results are located in these columns for each reaction and for each of the three media formulations. Media formulations are described below.
